parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive engine oil consumption can lead to premature wear on engine components, increased emissions, and higher maintenance costs. If left unchecked, it can also cause engine failure, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine burns oil at an excessive rate
soot or smoke coming out of the exhaust
oil soot or ash in the exhaust.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive oil consumption can lead to engine damage, increased emissions, and potentially cause the engine to seize or lock up, resulting in a loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Burning a quart of oil every 300-600 miles

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden failure of the rear wheel bearing can cause the rear wheel to seize, leading to a loss of control and potentially resulting in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: rear wheel locks up or seizes
